"Here is a new Python coding question for you:\n\n{\n\"title\": \"Maximum Sum Subarray (Hard)\",\n\"description\": \"Given an array of integers, find the maximum sum of a subarray within the given array. A subarray is a contiguous part of the array.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef max_sum_subarray(arr: list[int)) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `arr` (list[int]): An array of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the maximum sum of a subarray within the given array.\\n\",\n\"code\": \"\"\"\ndef max_sum_subarray(arr: list[int)) -> int:\n    if not arr:\n        return 0\n    \n    max_current = max_global = arr[0]\n    \n    for i in range(1, len(arr)):\n        max_current = max(0, max_current + arr[i])\n        \n        if max_current > max_global:\n            max_global = max_current\n        \n        max_current = max(arr[i], 0)\n    \n    return max_global\n\"\"\",\n\"tests\": [\n\"assert max_sum_subarray([-2,1,-3,4,-1,2,1,-5,4]) == 6\",\n\"assert max_sum_subarray([1,-2,3,10,-4,7,2,-5]) == 12\",\n\"assert max_sum_subarray([-1]) == -1\"\n]\n}\n\nLet me know if you want me to generate another question!"